Rubio is coming to Wisconsin on Nov. 9. By Patrick Marley of the Journal Sentinel Oct. 8, 2015 11:03 a.m. (0) Comments 
Madison — Just two months after Wisconsin Gov. Scott Walker abandoned his run for president, U.S. Sen. Marco Rubio will make foray into the Badger State in November. 
The Florida senator and GOP presidential contender will appear at a fundraiser Nov. 9 for Assembly Speaker Robin Vos (R-Rochester) and the campaign arm of Assembly Republicans. 
Rubio will speak at a roundtable event at the Veterans Terrace in Burlington moderated by WTMJ-AM (620) host Charlie Sykes. 
Attending the roundtable costs $2,500 per person and is limited to 20 people, according to a fundraising solicitation. That money will go to Republican Assembly Campaign Committee. 
Photos can be taken afterward for $500 per person, with those proceeds going to Vos' campaign. A $100-per-head reception for Vos will also be held that night at the Veterans Terrace in Burlington. 
Rubio's visit to Wisconsin is the first one announced by a GOP White House hopeful since Walker dropped out of the presidential race on Sept. 21.   About Patrick Marley 
Patrick Marley covers state government and state politics. He is the author, with Journal Sentinel reporter Jason Stein, of "More Than They Bargained For: Scott Walker, Unions and the Fight for Wisconsin.”
